  08 Jan 2010; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.3.ebuild, +files/sage-4.3-fix-deprecated-module.patch:
  Added a patch to fix importing of deprecated module "sets" in
  sqlalchemy and rewrote src_prepare to use new eclass function

  07 Jan 2010; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  -files/sage-4.2.1-singular-path-fix.patch, sage-4.3.ebuild,
  -files/sage-4.3-fix-rpy2.patch, -files/sage-4.3-use-R-from-portage.patch:
  Removed unneeded patches; removed ipython and polybori from Sage

  01 Jan 2010; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.3.ebuild:
  Removed python packages from Sage: pyprocessing, pygments, sympy,
  gdmodule and mpmath

  01 Jan 2010; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.3.ebuild:
  Removed rpy from Sage

  31 Dec 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  -sage-4.2.1.ebuild:
  Dropped old version

  30 Dec 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.3.ebuild:
  Removed cython and setuptools from Sage. This version may fail if one
  has Python packages installed that are also shipped with Sage

*sage-4.3 (28 Dec 2009)

  28 Dec 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  +sage-4.3.ebuild:
  Version bump

  28 Dec 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.1.ebuild:
  Packages removed from Sage: examples, rubiks

  21 Dec 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.1.ebuild:
  Removed symmetrica, no additional test failures

  19 Dec 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.1.ebuild:
  Removed packages from Sage and replaced with sage-data and sage-extcode

  19 Dec 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.1.ebuild:
  Force installation of older gfan - this may fix some tests

  18 Dec 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.1.ebuild:
  Fixed ECLDIR variable - now Sage should work with any version of
  ecls+maxima

  10 Dec 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.1.ebuild, +files/sage-4.2.1-amd64-hack.patch:
  Removed unsetting of ABI and moved unsets of C(XX)FLAGS to Sage's
  spkg-install file

  04 Dec 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.1.ebuild:
  Removed fortran stuff: lapack, blas

  01 Dec 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.1.ebuild, files/sage-4.2.1-singular-path-fix.patch:
  Added more documentation to the sed script which cleans Sage's makefile
  targets. Also adjust more singular paths. Singular will be built from
  Sage nevertheless, because libsingular has major differences to
  upstream

  01 Dec 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  -files/pari-2.3.3.p0-fix-ldconfig.patch, -sage-4.2.ebuild,
  sage-4.2.1.ebuild, -files/ecm-6.2.1.p0-fix-typo.patch,
  -files/deps-no-examples.patch, -files/eclib-fix-paths.patch,
  -files/g2red-pari-include-fix.patch, -files/install-no-doc.patch,
  -files/lcalc-fix-paths.patch, -files/linbox-fix-configure.patch,
  -files/sage-fix-paths.patch, -files/use-atlas-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-blas-from-portage.patch, -files/use-boehmgc-from-portage.patch,
  -files/use-bzip2-from-portage.patch,
