  +files/use-m4ri-from-portage.patch,
  +files/use-singular-from-portage.patch:
  Removed R and m4ri from sage, added experimental singular patches -
  they will need more testing

  23 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.1.ebuild, +files/use-eclib-from-portage.patch,
  +files/use-genus2reduction-from-portage.patch,
  +files/use-lcalc-from-portage.patch:
  Replaced packages from sage : eclib, lcalc, genus2reduction

*sage-4.2.1 (22 Nov 2009)

  22 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild, +sage-4.2.1.ebuild:
  Added new sage-4.2.1. Compiles fine on x86, not yet tested

  19 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild:
  Removed sage packages: mpir, libfplll, tachyon, ecm. Not yet tested.

  18 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild, metadata.xml:
  Adjusted pari paths: GPHELP and GPDOCDIR. Also unset compilation flags
  on amd64 for testing

  17 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de> ChangeLog:
  Changed ebuild to not use system fortran compiler if USE=sage-minimal
  and also to not remove documentation and examples. Disabled parallel
  make.

  16 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild:
  Successfully removed maxima and introduced a patch for pari-data which
  fixes at least one test. Also added some notes about further proceeding.

  12 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild:
  Removed disable-* USE flags and added new USE-flag: sage-minimal which
  uses only a minimal subset of packages from portage

  11 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild:
  Added use-flags disable-mpfr and disable-pari which should help finding
  bugs on amd64

  10 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild:
  Removed dependency on maxima as this package is used from sage, added
  some comments about what should be done in future and patched two files
  to correctly make a link sage_pari->(/usr/bin/)gp

  09 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild:
  Removed usage of R from portage because of test failures. Force sage to
  use Fortran compiler already installed and added some comments on maxima
  and python. Thanks to Francois Bissey for providing me this information!

  08 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild:
  Removed mpfi, givaro, iml, zn_poly and linbox from sage's dependencies and
  replaced by DEPENDs. Introduces no additional test failures.

  07 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild:
  Removed freetype and gd from sage's dependencies and replaced by DEPENDs.
  This breaks none of the tests

  05 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  sage-4.2.ebuild:
  Updated USE-flags, removed unneeded dependencies, temporarily falling
  back to sage maxima because sage could not start maxima from portage

  04 Nov 2009; Christopher Schwan <cschwan@students.uni-mainz.de>
  ChangeLog:
  Initial import - removed the following packages: atlas bzip2 gnutls gsl
  libpng maxima mercurial mpfr ntl pari R readline scons sqlite zlib

